She can see dead people…she just chooses to ignore them. That’s Miko’s plan, anyway, but it doesn’t seem to be working for her in this love letter to the horror genre that will send shivers down your spine—and occasionally tickle your funny bone.
(Source: Funimation)
Comedy, Drama, Romance, Slice of Life

The first time he saw her, it was love at first sight. Unfortunately for Sorata Kanda, "she" was a cat named Hikari and his school's rules forbid keeping pets in the regular dorms. As a result, Sorata is banished to the infamous Sakura Hall alongside other troublesome and unusual students like Jin, overzealous playboy, Ryuunosuke, the reclusive hermit, and Mashiro, a brilliant artist who's so unfocused and clueless about the real world that dorm supervisor Ms. Sengoku assigns Sorata the task of taking care of her along with his ever-growing collection of stray cats!
(Source: Sentai Filmworks)
Unmei de Musubareta Koibito......no Azatoi Imouto to Issen wo Koeteshimau, Ano Hi made

"If we reunite, let's be lovers"
That was the promise I made with my childhood friend, Mitsuha Mahiru a long time ago.
In the spring of my second year in high school, our fateful reunion happened. We exchanged our unchanging feelings and officially became a couple.
Just when I thought we could cohabitate blissfully at my place, another housemate - Mahiru's younger sister, Saya joined.
One night, I was kissed by Saya, who sneaked into my room.
"Shhh...be quiet. Let's keep this a secret"
From that moment, the cohabitation of three filled with secrecies began - till the day I eventually crossed the line with my lover's sister.
Kono Sankaku Love Come wa Shiawase ni Naru Gime ga Aru.

"What do you like about Reira so much?"

Tenma Yashiro, an ordinary high school boy, accidentally discovers that Rinka, a cool beauty in his class, is in love with his childhood friend, Reira Tsubaki, a beautiful and innocent girl. Tenma then helps Rinka become friends with Reira, but...

"If Yashiro-kun isn't dating Rinka-chan, then can I be your girlfriend instead?"

"What did you do, Yashiro?"

So Reira falls in love with Tenma, and a love triangle develops between him and the two most beautiful girls in school. What will happen in this complicated love story?

Winner of the 28th Dengeki Novel Award Gold Prize! The happiest love triangle in the history of romantic comedy begins!

(Source: Dengeki Bunko, translated)
